translated: Johnsson, Gustaf Leonard, director, Kalmar, born May 19, 1887 in Kristvalla, Kalmar County, son of Nils Gustaf J. and Maria Karlsdotter. Married on 1920 to Anna Elisabet Vilhelmina Melin. Children: Lars-Olof born in 1927. Director of the Kalmar County Employment Agency from 1937-1940, director of the County Labor Board in Kalmar since 1940. Member of the Swedish Parliament, second chamber, 1928 and 1933-1937; alternate member of the fourth committee 1928, member of the first legislative committee 1933-1937, and the fifth committee 1933-1937. Member of the county council since 1930, member of the council's administrative committee since 1930, member of the city council since 1917, vice-chairman 1920-1921, and Chairman since 1933. Member of the Finance Committee since 1919, and of the Lighting Board. Chairman of the Social Democratic Party District of Kalmar 1922-1946 and of the Kalmar Branch of the Swedish Metalworkers' Union 1910-1913 and 1915-1934. Member of the National Board of the Swedish Metalworkers' Union 1922-1937. Chairman of the Board of Directors of Kalmar Navigation Co. since 1944 and of the System A-B in Kalmar since 1939.
